questions.DESCRIBE THE EVENT, TRY TO INCLUDE HOW I: The event is structured to focus on three specific coding problems from LeetCode, selected to cover a range of difficulty levels and topics such as algorithms and data structures. This is aimed at enhancing students' problem-solving and coding skills by introducing them to best practices and efficient approaches to coding challenges. The workshop will include a detailed walkthrough of each problem, emphasizing optimal solutions and strategies like time complexity reduction and space optimization. Participants will learn how to approach different types of problems, identify common patterns, and apply appropriate algorithms. Additionally, the workshop is intended for students interested in programming and those preparing for technical interviews, offering insights into how tech companies evaluate coding proficiency.

questions.DESCRIBE THE EVENT, TRY TO INCLUDE HOW I:
This event is the first day of dress/tech rehearsals (2PM-6PM) for a performance in Spring Quarter in which Aequora Ballet Company members will dance classical and contemporary ballet choreography. The show will feature two other dance groups on campus, Muse Dance Company and Ikigai Dance Company.
The theme of the show is Alice in Wonderland interpretations. For company members, the event itself and preparation for it aim to improve students’ out-of-classroom experience by providing students with a social event, while promoting a balance of academics, personal growth, and extracurriculars. For potential attendees, the performance is an opportunity for students and the UCSD community at large to gain exposure to the arts–ballet specifically–and enrich their experience at UCSD with a live performance of ballet conveniently located on campus. Student attendees may also appreciate the opportunity of connecting with other peers who attend the performance, along with connecting with their dance-maker peers by witnessing their styles of storytelling through movement.  
Overall, Aequora Ballet Company aims to foster a diverse and inclusive classical and contemporary dance community for students to connect and improve their dancing, as well as the opportunity to perform in an annual showcase in which they can share their work with the UCSD community. This is our third year in-person as a student organization and fourth year overall, and we would use the funds to cover the Price Center venue and services.

questions.DESCRIBE THE EVENT, TRY TO INCLUDE HOW I: ACM at UCSD is UC San Diego's largest computing and tech organization, with over 1,500 members and over 200 technical, professional, and social events year-round. We’re not just limited to computer science, though — we bring together anyone and everyone who shares our love of technology, design, and innovation! Join us to find out how you can engage in our community for the Spring Quarter through socials, live coding workshops, tech talks, and much more. We welcome people of all backgrounds and skill levels, whether you’re an entry-level UI designer or a machine learning expert. Come be a part of our rapidly growing community of friends at our Spring Kickoff of the year! There will be free food and drinks so make sure to come by!!!! Join our discord to stay engaged with the community!

The URiM Conference is a free conference that will take place on Saturday, April 20th, 2023 from 7am-5:10pm. The mission of this conference is to provide undergraduate pre-health minority, first-generation, and lower SES students with some of the information, tools, and opportunities that are necessary to aid them in the process of reaching their healthcare career goals. 
Faculty, medical school students, and doctors from the UCSD School of Medicine are already confirmed to speak. We also have confirmed speakers with the Skaggs School of Pharmacy students as well as students from other programs. There will also be an Opportunities Fair where student organizations, UCSD Programs and organizations, and internship/volunteer programs will be tabling for students to explore.

questions.ORGANIZATION: Student Support Services Club (SSSC or SSS Club)
questions.DESCRIBE THE EVENT, TRY TO INCLUDE HOW I: Our organization provides a supportive space for students to interact and connect with each other through school events, learning environments (classroom and tutoring workshops), and personal associations throughout the year. For this reason, the mission statement of our organization is to empower underrepresented students in pursuing higher education and to celebrate cultural diversity. Each year our event has several components to follow our mission statement. Firstly, the event will gather the students in our organization who are from different backgrounds and UCSD colleges to celebrate their accomplishments and growth during the academic year. The event will also validate the achievements of the students in our organization and empower them as we come together as a community and support each other. For instance, the graduating seniors and their families, along with current club members will be recognized and honored for their achievements. In addition, the event will celebrate the diversity in the organization by having food catering that showcases the different cultures in our organization. Throughout the event, we will have a keynote speaker and a senior speaker who will inspire our students to succeed in higher education.
